headline: Menu suggestions for Obama and Romney's lunch
summary: Twitter users serve up some suggestions for President Obama and Mitt Romney's lunch tomorrow.

headline: Horrific N.C. crash puts spotlight on dram shop laws
summary: $1.7 million verdict in North Carolina drunken driving crash puts spotlight on "dram shop" laws, which vary across USA.

headline: Self-funding candidates fall short in Congress
summary: Self-funding candidates prove again and again that money is not enough to win an election.

headline: Iowa governor: Straw poll 'outlived usefulness'
summary: The Iowa Straw Poll is a GOP presidential ritual and fundraiser that goes back to 1979.

headline: Split-ticket voting popular in Montana, N.D.
summary: Montana and North Dakota voters backed Mitt Romney for president, but a Democrat for the U.S. Senate.

headline: Rep. Jesse Jackson Jr. resigns from Congress
summary: Democrat Jesse Jackson Jr. resigned from Congress amid separate investigations of wrongdoing.

headline: Romney supporters form immigration super PAC
summary: Carlos Gutierrez, a former Commerce secretary, says the new GOP group's goal is to pass an immigration bill.

headline: GOP candidate asks for recount in North Carolina
summary: State Sen. David Rouzer, R-N.C., says "accidental human error" could change the outcome in his race for Congress.

headline: Rand Paul 'interested' in 2016 presidential race
summary: The Kentucky senator, a Tea party favorite, has watched his dad run for the White House three times.

headline: Candidate wins coin flip, but council seat up in air
summary: A candidate whose wife couldn't vote on Election Day lost a tie-breaker but still might serve on his city's council.
